# Spring Voyage V2

An open-source collaboration platform for teams of AI agents — and the humans they work with. Built on .NET 10 and Dapr. Namespace: `Cvoya.Spring.*`.

**This is the open-source core platform.** A private repository (Spring Voyage Cloud) extends it via git submodule and DI to add multi-tenancy, OAuth, billing, and premium features. Design every change for clean extensibility — the private repo must be able to override, wrap, or compose OSS behavior without forking or patching.

## Essential References

- **Full conventions:** `CONVENTIONS.md` (MUST read before writing code)
- **Architecture:** `docs/architecture/README.md` (index of all architecture documents)
- **Extensibility model:** `AGENTS.md` § "Open-Source Platform & Extensibility"

## Quick Rules

- **Copyright header** on all C# files (see CONVENTIONS.md Section 0).
- **Namespace first, usings after:** file-scoped namespace immediately after copyright, then `using` statements.
- **Namespace = folder path:** `Cvoya.Spring.Core.Messaging` lives in `src/Cvoya.Spring.Core/Messaging/`
- **One public type per file.** File name matches type name.
- **`Cvoya.Spring.Core` has ZERO NuGet dependencies.** Domain abstractions only.
- **Interface-first:** define in `Cvoya.Spring.Core`, implement in `Cvoya.Spring.Dapr`.
- **System.Text.Json only.** No Newtonsoft.Json.
- **Primary constructor injection.** No service locator.
- **`TryAdd*` for all DI registrations** so the private repo can pre-register overrides.
- **`Async` suffix** on all async methods. `CancellationToken` as last parameter.
- **Never let exceptions escape actor turns.** Catch, log, update state.
- **Use `Result<T, TError>`** for expected failures (routing, resolution).
- **Don't seal extensible types.** Services, handlers, strategies, and base classes must remain unsealed.
- **No tenant concepts.** No `TenantId`, no multi-tenancy — the private repo layers that on.

## Build & Test

```bash
dotnet build
dotnet test
dotnet format --verify-no-changes
```

## Test Conventions

- xUnit + FluentAssertions + NSubstitute
- Test methods: `MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult`
- Use `ActorTestBase<TActor>` for actor tests
- Testcontainers for PostgreSQL integration tests

## Key Patterns

DI registration: `services.AddCvoyaSpringCore().AddCvoyaSpringDapr()`

State keys: centralized in `StateKeys` class (e.g., `StateKeys.ActiveConversation`)

Message handling: switch on `MessageType` in `ReceiveAsync`, delegate to typed handlers.

Logging: `ILogger<T>` with source-generated `LoggerMessage`. Event ID ranges per project (Core: 1000s, Dapr: 2000s, Host.Api: 3000s, Cli: 4000s, Connector.GitHub: 5000s).
